Parameters

Name
Type: SystemString
The name of a deck property. If this is an existing property, that property is modified; otherwise, a new property is added.
DeckType
Type: ETABSv1eDeckType
This is one of the following items in the eDeckType enumeration, which is Filled, Unfilled, or SolidSlab
SlabFillMatProp
Type: SystemString
The name of the material property for the slab/fill property. This applies if DeckType is Filled or SolidSlab
DeckMatProp
Type: SystemString
The name of the material property for the deck property. This applies if DeckType is Filled or Unfilled
SlabDepth
Type: SystemDouble
Slab Depth, tc. This applies if DeckType is Filled or SolidSlab
RibDepth
Type: SystemDouble
Rib Depth, hr. This applies if DeckType is Filled or Unfilled
RibWidthTop
Type: SystemDouble
Rib Width Top, wrt. This applies if DeckType is Filled or Unfilled
RibWidthBot
Type: SystemDouble
Rib Width Bottom, wrb. This applies if DeckType is Filled or Unfilled
RibSpacing
Type: SystemDouble
Rib Spacing, sr. This applies if DeckType is Filled or Unfilled
DeckShearThickness
Type: SystemDouble
Deck Shear Thickness. This applies if DeckType is Filled or Unfilled
DeckUnitWeight
Type: SystemDouble
Deck Unit Weight. This applies if DeckType is Filled or Unfilled
ShearStudDia
Type: SystemDouble
Shear Stud Diameter. This applies if DeckType is Filled or SolidSlab
ShearStudHs
Type: SystemDouble
Shear Stud Height, hs. This applies if DeckType is Filled or SolidSlab
ShearStudFu
Type: SystemDouble
Shear Stud Tensile Strength, Fu. This applies if DeckType is Filled or SolidSlab
color (Optional)
Type: SystemInt32
The display color assigned to the property.
notes (Optional)
Type: SystemString
The notes, if any, assigned to the property.
GUID (Optional)
Type: SystemString
The GUID (global unique identifier), if any, assigned to the property.

Return Value

Type: Int32
Returns zero if the property is successfully initialized; otherwise it returns a nonzero value.

Examples
VB
Copy
Public Sub Example()
       Dim SapModel As cSapModel
       Dim EtabsObject As cOAPI
       Dim ret As Integer = -1
       Dim Name As String
       Dim DeckType As eDeckType
       Dim SlabDepth As Double
       Dim RibDepth As Double
       Dim RibWidthTop As Double
       Dim RibWidthBot As Double
       Dim RibSpacing As Double
       Dim DeckShearThickness As Double
       Dim DeckUnitWeight As Double
       Dim ShearStudDia As Double
       Dim ShearStudHs As Double
       Dim ShearStudFu As Double
       Dim Color As Integer
       Dim Notes As String
       Dim GUID As String

   'create ETABS object
       Dim myHelper as cHelper = New Helper
       EtabsObject = myHelper.CreateObjectProgID("CSI.ETABS.API.ETABSObject")

   'start ETABS application
       ret = EtabsObject.ApplicationStart()

   'create SapModel object
       SapModel = EtabsObject.SapModel

   'initialize model
       ret = SapModel.InitializeNewModel()

   'create steel deck template model
       ret = SapModel.File.NewSteelDeck(4,12,12,4,4,24,24)

       Name = "MyShellProp1A"
       DeckType = eDeckType.Filled
       SlabFillMatProp = "4000Psi"
       DeckMatProp = "A992Fy50"
       SlabDepth = 15.6
       RibDepth = 1.1
       RibWidthTop = 2.3
       RibWidthBot = 2.4
       RibSpacing = 7
       DeckShearThickness = 5
       DeckUnitWeight = 3.1
       ShearStudDia = 1.02
       ShearStudHt = 4.4
       ShearStudFu = 2.01
       ret = mySapModel.PropArea.SetDeck_1(Name, DeckType, SlabFillMatProp, DeckMatProp, SlabDepth, RibDepth, RibWidthTop, RibWidthBot, RibSpacing, DeckShearThickness, DeckUnitWeight, ShearStudDia, ShearStudHt, ShearStudFu, color, notes, GUID)

       DeckType = eDeckType.SolidSlab
       SlabFillMatProp = ""
       DeckMatProp = ""
       SlabDepth = 0
       RibDepth = 0
       RibWidthTop = 0
       RibWidthBot = 0
       RibSpacing = 0
       DeckShearThickness = 0
       DeckUnitWeight = 0
       ShearStudDia = 0
       ShearStudHt = 0
       ShearStudFu = 0
    'get area property data
       ret = mySapModel.PropArea.GetDeck_1(Name, DeckType, SlabFillMatProp, DeckMatProp, SlabDepth, RibDepth, RibWidthTop, RibWidthBot, RibSpacing, DeckShearThickness, DeckUnitWeight, ShearStudDia, ShearStudHt, ShearStudFu, color, notes, GUID)

   'close ETABS
       EtabsObject.ApplicationExit(False)

   'clean up variables
       SapModel = Nothing
       EtabsObject = Nothing
   End Sub
